{"header":"<h1>Module <code><span>Expr.Subst</span></code></h1>","type":"documentation","uses_katex":false,"breadcrumbs":[{"name":"Index","href":"../../../../../../../../../index.html","kind":"leaf-page"},{"name":"soteria","href":"../../../../../../../../index.html","kind":"page"},{"name":"Soteria","href":"../../../../../../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Data","href":"../../../../../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"S_map","href":"../../../../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Mk_concrete_key","href":"../../../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Symex","href":"../../../index.html","kind":"argument-1"},{"name":"Value","href":"../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Expr","href":"../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Subst","href":"#","kind":"module"}],"toc":[],"source_anchor":null,"preamble":"<p>A susbtitution projects the syntactic to the semantic world.</p>","content":"<div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec type subst anchored\" id=\"type-expr\"><a href=\"#type-expr\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">type</span> expr</span><span> := <a href=\"../index.html#type-t\">t</a></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec type anchored\" id=\"type-t\"><a href=\"#type-t\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">type</span> t</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Type of substitutions</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-pp\"><a href=\"#val-pp\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> pp : <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><a href=\"#type-t\">t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-empty\"><a href=\"#val-empty\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> empty : <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-apply\"><a href=\"#val-apply\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> apply : <span><span class=\"label\">missing_var</span>:<span>(<span><a href=\"../../../../../../../Symex/Var/index.html#type-t\">Symex.Var.t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"../../index.html#type-ty\">ty</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"../../index.html#type-t\">t</a></span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><a href=\"#type-t\">t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><a href=\"#type-expr\">expr</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"../../index.html#type-t\">t</a></span> * <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Applies a substitution to a syntactic representation to obtain a symbolic value. Should a variable binding be missing, fresh values are generated using the provided function.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-learn\"><a href=\"#val-learn\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> learn : <span><a href=\"#type-t\">t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><a href=\"#type-expr\">expr</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"../../index.html#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><a href=\"#type-t\">t</a> option</span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>learn θ e v</code> takes the substitution <code>θ</code>, the expression <code>e</code> and the value <code>v</code> and tries to complete <code>θ</code> into a substitution <code>θ'</code> such that <code>θ'(e) = v</code>.</p><p>The only requirement from this function is that, if this function returns <code>Some θ'</code>, then <code>θ'</code> covers all variables in <code>e</code>. However, all implementations of this function should be sound:</p><ul><li>If this function returns a substitution that does not cover all variables in <code>e</code>, the client may crash (but not result to an unsoundness).</li><li>If this function returns a wrong substitution (where <code>θ'(e) != v</code>), this will not result in an unsoundness, but may prevent successful consumption.</li><li>If there are multiple substitutions that satisfy the requirement, this function can return any of them. This will lead to under-approximation when in UX mode, and to a probable consumption failure in UX mode.</li><li>If this function returns <code>None</code> when there exists a correct substitution, this will only lead to consumption failure. The function can always be extended to return a correct substitution.</li></ul></div></div>"}